// =============================================================================
// SRE Agent Operational Telemetry (SCHEMA_TBD)
// =============================================================================
// Purpose: Query SRE Agent App Insights telemetry for conversations, actions, errors
// Use case: Audit agent behavior, troubleshoot agent issues, measure diagnosis time (T2→T3)
// Time range: Configurable via TimeRange parameter (default: last 24 hours)
// Parameters:
//   - TimeRange: Time window for analysis (default: 24h)
//   - timeBin: Time bucket granularity for trending (default: 15m)
//
// ⚠️ SCHEMA_TBD — Azure SRE Agent Preview (2025-05-01-preview)
//
// WARNING: This query references SRE Agent App Insights telemetry fields that are
// subject to change during Public Preview. Field names, dimensions, and schema may
// change without notice before GA.
//
// PHYSICAL SEPARATION: This query lives under docs/evidence/kql/schema-tbd/ to
// isolate Preview-dependent queries from stable Container Insights/Activity Log queries.
// Per Security SR-2, stable queries must not reference SCHEMA_TBD fields.
//
// Known TBD fields (observed in 2025-05-01-preview, subject to change):
//   - customDimensions["sre.agent.conversationId"]
//   - customDimensions["sre.agent.action"]
//   - customDimensions["sre.agent.recommendation"]
//   - operation_Name (may contain agent-specific operation types)
//   - dependency telemetry (how agent queries Log Analytics, ARM, etc.)
//
// Required projected columns: TimeBucket, ResourceId, CorrelationId (per Security MF-3)
//
// For contract details, see: docs/CAPABILITY-CONTRACTS.md §8 (SCHEMA_TBD Rule)
// =============================================================================

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// PARAMETERS — Modify before running
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
let TimeRange = 24h;           // Parameter: Time window
let timeBin = 15m;             // Parameter: Time bucket granularity for trending

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// QUERY LOGIC — SCHEMA_TBD
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// SCHEMA_TBD — Conversation traces (if agent emits custom dimensions)
traces
| where timestamp > ago(TimeRange)
| where cloud_RoleName contains "sre-agent" or customDimensions has "sre.agent"
| extend
    // SCHEMA_TBD — Field names are subject to change
    ConversationId = tostring(customDimensions["sre.agent.conversationId"]),
    Action = tostring(customDimensions["sre.agent.action"]),
    Recommendation = tostring(customDimensions["sre.agent.recommendation"]),
    // Security MF-3 required columns
    TimeBucket = bin(timestamp, timeBin),
    ResourceId = column_ifexists("_ResourceId", ""),  // App Insights app resource ID
    CorrelationId = column_ifexists("operation_Id", "")  // App Insights operation correlation
| project
    TimeBucket,
    timestamp,
    message,
    severityLevel,
    ConversationId,
    Action,
    Recommendation,
    ResourceId,
    CorrelationId,
    customDimensions
| order by timestamp desc

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// ADDITIONAL QUERIES (Commented — Uncomment after schema verification)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// SCHEMA_TBD — Dependency calls from SRE Agent to Log Analytics, ARM, etc.
// dependencies
// | where timestamp > ago(TimeRange)
// | where cloud_RoleName contains "sre-agent"
// | extend
//     TargetService = tostring(target),
//     DependencyType = tostring(type),
//     Duration = duration,
//     TimeBucket = bin(timestamp, timeBin),
//     ResourceId = column_ifexists("_ResourceId", ""),
//     CorrelationId = column_ifexists("operation_Id", "")
// | project
//     TimeBucket,
//     timestamp,
//     name,
//     TargetService,
//     DependencyType,
//     Duration,
//     success,
//     resultCode,
//     ResourceId,
//     CorrelationId
// | order by timestamp desc

// SCHEMA_TBD — Exceptions and errors
// exceptions
// | where timestamp > ago(TimeRange)
// | where cloud_RoleName contains "sre-agent"
// | extend
//     TimeBucket = bin(timestamp, timeBin),
//     ResourceId = column_ifexists("_ResourceId", ""),
//     CorrelationId = column_ifexists("operation_Id", "")
// | project
//     TimeBucket,
//     timestamp,
//     type,
//     outerMessage,
//     problemId,
//     ResourceId,
//     CorrelationId,
//     customDimensions
// | order by timestamp desc

// =============================================================================
// Wave 1 UAT Verification Plan
// =============================================================================
//
// BEFORE SRE Agent is deployed:
// - This query will return no results (App Insights has no agent telemetry yet)
// - UAT step: Verify query syntax is valid (no parsing errors)
//
// AFTER SRE Agent is deployed (with appInsightsConnectionString configured):
// 1. Deploy infrastructure with deploySreAgent = true
// 2. Open SRE Agent portal and submit a test prompt (e.g., "Show me pods in energy namespace")
// 3. Wait 2-5 minutes for telemetry ingestion
// 4. Run this query in Log Analytics workspace
// 5. Expected results:
//    - traces table has entries with cloud_RoleName or customDimensions related to SRE Agent
//    - TimeBucket, ResourceId, CorrelationId columns are populated (per Security MF-3)
//    - If no results, check App Insights connection in sre-agent.bicep deployment
//    - If results appear but field names differ, update SCHEMA_TBD comments
//
// 6. Document observed field names in docs/evidence/kql/README.md with:
//    - API version: 2025-05-01-preview
//    - Date observed: YYYY-MM-DD
//    - Field name: customDimensions["actual.field.name"]
//    - Purpose: what the field represents
//
// 7. Tag any new queries using these fields with // SCHEMA_TBD comments
//
// KNOWN LIMITATIONS:
// - SRE Agent conversation history retention: Unknown (Preview service)
// - App Insights sampling: May impact telemetry volume at high scale
// - Cross-region latency: telemetry may take 2-10 minutes to appear
//
// =============================================================================
